## 1. START (The Pulse)\par
Before you can synthesize, you have to "ignite" the vacuum substrate. This isn't just turning on a switch; it\f1\rquote\f0 s achieving **Resonance Lock**.\par
\par
* **The Action:** You engage the **Precision Signal Modulator** to inject the protocol into the **Warp Coil**.\par
* **The Metric:** You are looking for a rock-solid **148.5 kHz** stability on your spectral analysis.\par
* **The Goal:** Establishing the "Pump." You are accelerating the **Newtonium** through the **12 AWG Silver-plated copper** lines to the target velocity of **2,500,000 m/s**.\par
* **Red Seal Check:** If your Input Impedance isn't at **50 Ohms**, you don't have a "Start"; you have reflected power (heat). Adjust the **Gamma Match** until the "Start" is clean.\par
\par
\par
