## 2. STEER (The Lattice)\par
Once the system is "running," you have to guide the ballistic transport through the **Null-Point**. Without steering, the energy just dissipates as heat.\par
\par
* **The Action:** This is where the **N52 Magnetic Arrays** and the **64-bit Belnap-W logic** come in. You are "steering" the flux lines to create the hexagonal compression.\par
* **The Metric:** Geometric consistency. You use the `hex_coords.py` model to ensure the magnets are seated to within **$\\pm 0.0001"$ ($0.0025 \\text\{ mm\}$)**.\par
* **The Goal:** Directing the high-velocity particles into the **Isostatic Graphite** medium. You are forcing the "Changing Lines" of the physical hexagram into a stable 4-valued logic state (True, False, Both, Neither).\par
* **Red Seal Check:** If the **PEEK Jig** is slightly warped, your steering is "pulling to the left." The manifestation won't center in the bore.\par
\par
