### \f2\u-10179?\u-8495?\b\f1  \f0 THE 3 S SHUTDOWN PROCEDURE\b0\par
\par
#### **1. STOP (The Frequency Brake)**\par
*Goal: Decelerate the resonance and collapse the standing wave.*\par
* **Action:** Gradually ramp down the **Precision Signal Modulator** from the 148.5 kHz lock.\par
* **The Metric:** Watch the Spectrum Analyzer. You want to see the **25 MHz sub-harmonic** decay linearly. Do not cut power abruptly; this prevents an inductive "kick" in the **Litz Wire** Weft coil.\par
* **The Goal:** Bringing the "Newtonium" transit to a full halt within the **Isostatic Graphite** medium.\par
\par
\par
#### **2. STEER (The Field Dissipation)**\par
*Goal: Neutralize the magnetic pressure and clear the logic gates.*\par
* **Action:** Power down the **Halbach-array modulators** (if using electromagnets) or safely retract the **N52 Hex-Array** from the Jig.\par
* **The Metric:** Use the Gauss meter to verify the center-bore flux drops from **1.48 Tesla** back to ambient levels.\par
* **The Goal:** Clearing the "Steering" vectors so the **Synthetic Quartz Resonator** can return to its natural mechanical state without stress.\par
* **Logic Wipe:** Command the FPGA to a "Null" state. Ensure all **Belnap-W** registers are cleared to prevent "Ghost States" in the next run.\par
\par
#### **3. START (The Reset/Standby)**\par
*Goal: Secure the hardware for the next "Start" cycle.*\par
* **Action:** Physically inspect the **PEEK Jig** and **12 AWG Warp Coil** for any thermal discoloration or vibration-induced loosening.\par
* **The Metric:** Check the **Z-axis zero-datum**. Ensure the mandrel hasn't migrated due to the magnetic compression forces.\par
* **The Goal:** Re-establishing the "Ready" state. Lock the **64-bit stack** and disconnect the primary power lead.\par
